When user says `/seo-master`, follow `skills/seo-master/SKILL.md`.

**Invocation**: `/seo-master [site path or URL]`

**Steps**:
1. Detect the stack (Next.js App/Pages Router, React SPA, Astro…) — `references/framework-seo.md`.
2. Map target AI engines/agents to their index (Bing/Brave/Google) — `references/ai-engines-and-indexes.md`.
3. Audit, then fix: indexing reach → structured data → answer-first content → titles/meta → content moat.

**Critical**:
- Detect framework before implementing — Next.js uses the Metadata API, not prerender.
- Never fabricate aggregateRating/reviews; FAQ schema requires visible on-page FAQ.
- Coding agents (Claude Code/Codex/OpenClaw) ground on Brave — keep clean server HTML.
- Don't over-optimize for AI citations (May 2026 core update risk); llms.txt is optional.
